'''Tharwat Bassily''' ''Ph.D.'', (14 September 1940 &ndash; 5 December 2017) was an Egyptian businessman, he graduated from the Faculty of Pharmacy, Cairo University in 1967,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.akhbarak.net/news/2017/12/05/12994212/articles/27668940/%D9%85%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%88%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%B9%D9%86-%D8%B1%D8%AC%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B9%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%81%D9%89-%D8%AB%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8A|title=معلومات عن رجل الأعمال المصري المتوفى|work=أخبارك.نت|access-date=2018-03-14|language=ar}}</ref> also he was founder and Chairman of the Board of '''Amoun Pharmaceutical Company''' S.A.E., one of the leading private pharmaceutical companies in [[Egypt]]. He was also the undersecretary of the [[Holy Synod of the Coptic Orthodox Church]],<ref>{{cite news|title= Investigations exclude possibility of crime in disappearance of priest’s wife|url=http://www.almasryalyoum.com/en/news/investigations-exclude-possibility-crime-disappearance-priest%E2%80%99s-wife|accessdate=5 August 2010|newspaper=[[Almasry Alyoum]]|date=24 July 2010}}</ref> a member of the [[Shura Council]],<ref>{{cite news|title=44 Shura appointments include 8 Copts |url=http://www.almasryalyoum.com/en/news/44-shura-appointments-include-8-copts|accessdate=5 August 2010|newspaper=[[Almasry Alyoum]]|date=22 June 2010}}</ref> and the founder of [[Coptic TV]].<ref>{{cite web|title= Egypt: Who really needs Coptic TV?|url=http://www.menassat.com/?q=en/news-articles/2395-egypt-who-really-needs-coptic-tv|publisher=Menassat.com|accessdate=5 August 2010}}</ref> ==External links== * [http://www.amoun.com Amoun Pharmaceutical Company] * [http://www.ctvchannel.tv/ ctv channel]
